d5df4bff-2273-5e2a-ad2f-3a141849035c,tg:rubgr:504,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Ad [Addendum] Dulle Griet. Marcus Gheeraerts, Allegory of Iconoclasm, etching unique example in Br.Mus. (cannot be found); A.J.J. Delen, Histoire de la Gravure...[dans les anciens Pays-Bas & dans les provinces belges: des origines jusqu'à la fin du XVIIIe siècle], II/2: Les Graveurs-Illustrateurs, Paris [Editions d'art et d'histoire], 1934, pl. LVI; D. [David] A. Freedberg, Iconoclasm and Painting in the Netherlands, 1566-1609, Oxford, Ph.D. thesis 1972, p. 186f, pl. 1. Presupposes knowledge of Dulle Griet. General head form and especially snake in nostril, cf. my assumption is correct, one could from M. Gheeraert's dates conclude when Bruegel's painting was still in the Netherlands & Hollstein N°? see also E. [Edward] HODNETT,  Marcus Gheeraerts the Elder of Bruges, London, and Antwerp, Utrecht [Haentjens Dekker & Gumbert], 1971, p. 27; (Also A. Schouteet, Marcus Gerards [zestiende-eeuws schilder en graveur], Bruges [Gidsenbond],1941) [...]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
